# ExamSpark Core Rules (MUST FOLLOW)

Full spec: [`PROJECT_CORE_RULES.md`](PROJECT_CORE_RULES.md)

## Storage

- **Temp (delete after processing):** Raw audio, temp AI/OCR files, upload cache
- **R2 permanent:** Notes, Summary, Flashcards, Quiz, transcripts, PDF, images, teacher files
- **Postgres:** Metadata only — never large blobs
- **Vectors:** Clean Transcript chunks + AI Notes + Teacher Shared Notes only
- Audio: delete after Whisper unless teacher `Save Original Audio` ON

## Groups

- Teacher owns group; students **cannot** upload, message, or edit
- Teacher photo + name visible; description; pinned on top

## Sharing (Strict)

- **Only teacher** shares content (notes, PDF, quiz, etc.)
- Students **cannot** share/export/forward/download protected content
- Students **may only** share **Group Invite Link** (future: 100 credits configurable)
- Watermark shared content: `Shared by: {Teacher} • {Group}` + `lecture_id` traceability

## RAG Priority (never skip order)

1. User Notes → 2. Transcript (clean chunks) → 3. Teacher Shared → 4. Web Search

## PYQ

- Mapping only — exam reference tags (NEET 2024, etc.)
- **Never** show original Q/options/answer key/explanation

## Cost & Security

- No duplicate vectors/notes; reuse RAG; minimize storage
- Students isolated; groups isolated; permission check every AI request
- Modular adapters — models, storage, payments replaceable
